Paul Bernard Rodgers (born 17 December 1949) is an English-Canadian
rock singer-songwriter, best known for his success in the 1970s as
vocalist of Free and Bad Company. After stints in two less successful
bands in the 1980s and early 1990s, The Firm and The Law, he became a
solo artist. He has more recently toured and recorded with another
popular band, Queen. Rodgers has been dubbed "The Voice" by his fans.
A poll in Rolling Stone magazine ranked him number 55 on its list of
the "100 Greatest Singers of All Time"
